'''戴夫·考兹'''（{{lang|en|Dave Koz}}，{{bd|1963年|3月27日||}}）是一位美国轻柔爵士萨克斯吹奏者。

==早期生活==
1963年3月27日戴夫·考兹出生于[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]恩西诺市，父母是犹太人，父亲诺曼是皮肤科医生，母亲奥黛丽哈是药剂师。大卫有一个弟弟杰夫和一个妹妹罗伯塔，杰夫也是一个音乐家。<ref>{{cite news|last=Ford|first=Dave|url=http://www.sfgate.com/entertainment/article/Record-exec-radio-star-and-smooth-jazz-man-Dave-2700282.php|title=Record exec, radio star and smooth-jazz man. Dave Koz now settles into his newest groove: being an out gay man|date=August 20, 2004|publisher=sfgate.com|accessdate=2013-11-29|archive-date=2021-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210214005117/https://www.sfgate.com/entertainment/article/Record-exec-radio-star-and-smooth-jazz-man-Dave-2700282.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>尽管他是犹太人，考兹偶会在他的音乐会上演奏圣诞节和光明节歌曲。<ref>{{cite news|last=Akamatsu|first=Rhetta|url=http://www.seattlepi.com/lifestyle/blogcritics/article/Concert-Review-Dave-Koz-and-Friends-Christmas-2296128.php|title=Concert Review: Dave Koz and Friends Christmas, Cobb Energy Performing Arts Center, Atlanta, GA11/25/11|date=November 27, 2011|publisher=seattlepi.com|accessdate=2013-11-29|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125143733/https://www.seattlepi.com/lifestyle/blogcritics/article/Concert-Review-Dave-Koz-and-Friends-Christmas-2296128.php|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Condran|first=Ed|url=http://www.newsobserver.com/2013/11/28/3409998/dave-koz-brings-christmas-spirit.html|title=Dave Koz brings Christmas spirit to Durham|date=November 28, 2013|publisher=newsobserver.com|accessdate=2013-11-29|archive-date=2013-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131207093326/http://www.newsobserver.com/2013/11/28/3409998/dave-koz-brings-christmas-spirit.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>他入讀加利福尼亚洛杉矶林地山（Woodland Hills）的[[威廉霍华德塔夫脱特许高中|威廉霍华德塔夫脱特许高中]]，是校內爵士乐队演奏萨克斯的成員。1986年他以[[大众传媒|大众传媒]]学位毕业于[[加州大学洛杉矶分校|加州大学洛杉矶分校]]，毕业后只有几周就决定成为一名专业的音乐家。

==职业生涯==
毕业没几周，他被招募成为[[鲍比·考德威尔|鲍比·考德威尔]]巡回演出的成员。1980年代末，考兹在几个乐队中担任[[录音乐师|录音乐师]]和[[杰夫·罗伯|杰夫·罗伯]]（Jeff Lorber）一起巡回演出。在1980年代末和1990年代初，考兹是[[理查·马克斯|理查·马克斯]]乐队的成员並一起巡回演出。他还在[[哥伦比亚广播公司|哥伦比亚广播公司]]（CBS）的[[The_Pat_Sajak_Show|The Pat Sajak Show]]中演奏，[[汤姆·斯科特|汤姆·斯科特]]担任领队。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=19910628&slug=1291538 |title=Pack A Picnic And Head For Ste. Michelle's Big Outdoor Concert, The Seattle Times, June 28, 1991 |access-date=2015-03-17 |archive-date=2013-12-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213214139/http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=19910628&slug=1291538 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1990年，考兹决定单飞，并开始為[[Capitol唱片|国会唱片]]（Capitol Records）录制。他的专辑包括《[[幸运的男人|幸运的男人]]》、《舞蹈》、《[[Saxophonic|Saxophonic]]》。Saxophonic被提名[[葛萊美獎|格莱美奖]]和[[有色人种促进协会形象奖|有色人种促进协会形象奖]]。1994年，考兹开始主持一個[[廣播聯賣|廣播聯賣]]電台节目，「戴夫·考兹的广播节目」（Dave Koz Radio Show，以前稱「个人笔记」），是關於最近的音乐和访谈。戴夫在洛杉矶一間轻柔爵士電台「94.7电台」共同主持「戴夫·考兹早间节目」（The Dave Koz Morning Show）長達六年。2007年1月他决定离开这个节目，由[[布莱恩·麦肯奈特|布莱恩·麦肯奈特]]接替。2002年考兹与[[弗兰克·科迪|弗兰克·科迪]]和海曼·卡茨开設了一家唱片公司「相约娱乐」（Rendezvous Entertainment）。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2002/sep/26/news/wk-family26 |title='Family' CD Puts Them to Sleep; 'Golden Slumber,' lullabies from Dave Koz and his smooth-jazz collaborators, is the first release on his new record label |newspaper=The Los Angeles Times |date=September 26, 2002 |first=Lynne |last=Heffley |accessdate=2015-03-17 |archive-date=2013-12-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131230235116/http://articles.latimes.com/2002/sep/26/news/wk-family26 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[File:Wayman_Tisdale_&_Dave_Koz.jpg|thumb]]

2006年，考兹被选中为Broadcast Architecture公司举办的新爵士乐网络午后节目擔任主持。这个演出以洛杉矶為基地，在全国其它爵士乐电台播出。在一周中，考兹和[[拉姆齐·刘易斯|拉姆齐·刘易斯]]是仅有的两个柔和爵士乐人物擔任主持，分别主持两个不同的节目。国会唱片/百代唱片的“Forever Cool”（2007年）突出了考兹在编曲中加入了后[[迪恩马丁|迪恩马丁]]的新风格。

自2005年以来，考兹加入了一年一度的戴夫·考兹与朋友的柔和爵士乐巡演。

考兹主持了名为Frequency的每周半小时的电视访谈节目。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fastfocus.tv/Media.aspx?id=290|title=Frequency – Hosted by Dave Koz|work=fastfocus.tv|publisher=Public Television Media|accessdate=2009-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090629152806/http://www.fastfocus.tv/media.aspx?id=290|archive-date=2009-06-29|dead-url=yes}}</ref>考兹采访的音乐家有[[地，風與火|地，風與火]]、[[乔纳森·巴特勒|乔纳森·巴特勒]]和[[凯利·斯威|凯利·斯威]]。在每次采访结束之前，他都会和受采访的音乐家一起表演，在他们的热门歌曲中添加一些萨克斯管即兴演出。

考兹也是[[The_Emeril_Lagasse_Show|The Emeril Lagasse Show]]的樂隊领班。这个乐队Dave Koz & The Kozmos的成員有吉他手Jeff Golub、键盘手Philippe Saisse、低音吉他手Conrad Korsch和鼓手Skoota Warner。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.davidmixner.com/2010/03/television-emeril-lagasse-and-dave-koz.html|title=Television: Emeril Lagasse and Dave Koz|date=March 22, 2010|accessdate=May 10, 2010|archive-date=2016-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160720124050/http://www.davidmixner.com/2010/03/television-emeril-lagasse-and-dave-koz.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://jazztimes.com/articles/25803-dave-koz-and-emeril-team-up-on-tv|title=Dave Koz and Emeril Team Up on TV|author=Aubrey Everett|publisher=[[JazzTimes|JazzTimes]]|date=March 4, 2010|accessdate=May 17, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100329091719/http://jazztimes.com/articles/25803-dave-koz-and-emeril-team-up-on-tv|archive-date=2010-03-29|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ionpress.com/Emeril/pdf/Emeril_Dave-Koz-and-Kozmos-Bio.pdf|title=Dave Koz & The Kozmos|accessdate=May 10, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120306132058/http://www.ionpress.com/Emeril/pdf/Emeril_Dave-Koz-and-Kozmos-Bio.pdf|archive-date=2012-03-06|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

考兹演奏往往使用一个雅马哈中音萨克斯搭配比才尔七号金属喉舌，或者一个雅马哈降B高音萨克斯搭配8号Couf喉舌，又或者埃马克6次中音萨克斯管搭配一个Berg-Larsen 90/2硬橡胶喉舌。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wwbw.com/What-the-Pros-Play---Dave-Koz-g26484t0.wwbw |title=What the Pros Play – Saxophonist Dave Koz |last=Vail |first=Greg |accessdate=March 2, 2014 |publisher=Woodwind & Brasswind |archive-date=2016-10-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018204507/http://www.wwbw.com/What-the-Pros-Play---Dave-Koz-g26484t0.wwbw |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2009年9月22日，考兹在[[好莱坞星光大道|好莱坞星光大道]]（Hollywood Walk of Fame）收到一颗星。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/Arts_and_Entertainment/Music/Koz_Celeb|title=Koz Celeb|last=Steele|first=Bruce|work=[[The_Advocate|The Advocate]]|date=September 22, 2009|accessdate=May 17, 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091003221131/http://www.advocate.com/Arts_and_Entertainment/Music/Koz_Celeb|archivedate=2009年10月3日}}</ref>

2010年10月，考兹在《[[绝望的主妇|绝望的主妇]]》第七季插曲“Let Me Entertain You”中与歌手Dana Glover一同演奏“Start All Over Again”。2012年7月，他在The Eric André Show第1季第7集登場，坐在乐队中。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.amazon.com/J-Moe/dp/B008J3KUKUm |title=The Eric André Show, Season 1, Episode 7, 'J-Moe' |publisher=Amazon |accessdate=October 22, 2014 }}</ref>

2014年12月，他开了Spaghettini & the Dave Koz Lounge，是一个內有现场音乐演出的餐厅，位于加州比佛利山庄的184 North Canon Drive，合作伙伴还有[[Cary_Hardwick|Cary Hardwick]]和[[Laurie_Sisneros|Laurie Sisneros]]，他们在西尔滩开了Spaghettini。<ref>Matt Lopez, 'Spaghettini Beverly Hills Set To Open With Performance By Santana's Andy Vargas', ''[[TheBeverly_Hills_Courier|TheBeverly Hills Courier]]'', December 5, 2014, Volume XXXXVIIII, Number 48, p. 4</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.spaghettinibh.com/about.php |title=Spaghettini & the Dave Koz Lounge Beverly Hills |access-date=2015-03-17 |archive-date=2018-11-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181124105637/http://www.spaghettinibh.com/about.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==个人生活==
2004年4月在The Advocate杂志一次采访中，考兹公开自己是同性恋。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.advocate.com/arts-entertainment/music/2009/09/22/koz-celeb?page=full|work=The Advocate|title=Koz Celeb|date=September 22, 2009|accessdate=August 21, 2013|quote="his first CD of all-new, original material since he came out in ''The Advocate'' in 2004"|archive-date=2020-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205084226/https://www.advocate.com/arts-entertainment/music/2009/09/22/koz-celeb?page=full|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.questia.com/library/1G1-116225047/just-koz-smooth-jazz-golden-boy-dave-koz-comes-out-fresh|title=Just Koz: Smooth-Jazz Golden Boy Dave Koz Comes Out-Fresh off His Adventurous New Album, Saxophonic|work=The Advocate {{Subscription required |via=[[Questia|Questia]]}}|date=April 27, 2004|accessdate=August 21, 2013|last=Vary|first=Adam B.|quote=Credibility is one of the main reasons why I feel like now is the time to bring [my sexuality] to my music, to my professional life.... I couldn't actually be who I really was, and I went along with it for a long time, until it was just too much to take, and I couldn't deal with that anymore.|archive-date=2013-12-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213231046/http://www.questia.com/library/1G1-116225047/just-koz-smooth-jazz-golden-boy-dave-koz-comes-out-fresh|dead-url=no}}</ref>

